entries.femaleVariant: Jeez, mom... Mommm, stop being so twentieth-century!
No, ugh, I'm not tryin' to be "nova." It's about expression, Mom. You won't let me express myself!
They're like, chemical implants. Put 'em under a few layers of skin, they emit whatever light they absorb.
Why not? Kelsey's cousin is a Microtech agent, nobody cares that she has one.
When I'm older? Let's see if I live that long first. And if I change my mind, I can just swap my skin.
Mom, seriously, really don't see what the big deal is.
